{% extends 'layouts/page.njk' %}

{% block content %}
  {{ appHeading({
    text: heading,
    caption: "Surveillance Data Orchestration (SDO) Portal"
  }) }}

  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <div class="govuk-body" data-testid="app-page-body">
        <p class="govuk-body-l">
          The Surveillance Data Orchestration (SDO) project enhances the detection, assessment, and mitigation of disease-related threats to livestock and wildlife in Great Britain.
        </p>

        <a href="/oidc-signin" class="govuk-button govuk-button--start" data-module="govuk-button">
          Sign in to SDO Portal
          <svg class="govuk-button__start-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="17.5" height="19" viewBox="0 0 33 40" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
            <path fill="currentColor" d="m0 0h13l20 20-20 20H0l20-20z"></path>
          </svg>
        </a>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What SDO does</h2>
        <p>
          SDO is part of the Scanning Surveillance Development Programme (SSDP), led by the Animal and Plant Health Agency (APHA). It provides a comprehensive and integrated approach to veterinary surveillance through modern data management and analytical tools.
        </p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Key features</h2>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li><strong>Data Integration:</strong> Unified platform for APHA and external data sources</li>
          <li><strong>Advanced Analytics:</strong> Centralised data lake with Medallion Architecture (Bronze, Silver, Gold layers)</li>
          <li><strong>Automated Workflows:</strong> Streamlined data pipelines for efficient processing</li>
          <li><strong>Secure Governance:</strong> Enhanced data security protocols and compliance</li>
          <li><strong>Disease Monitoring:</strong> Real-time surveillance and outbreak detection</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="govuk-inset-text">
          <p>This system is for authorised APHA personnel and approved external partners involved in veterinary surveillance activities.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-third">
      <div class="govuk-body">
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Quick links</h2>
        <ul class="govuk-list">
          <li><a href="/oidc-signin" class="govuk-link">Sign in</a></li>
          <li><a href="/dashboard" class="govuk-link">Dashboard</a></li>
          <li><a href="/contact" class="govuk-link">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">For external partners</h3>
        <p class="govuk-body-s">
          If you're an external partner needing access to submit surveillance data, please contact your APHA liaison officer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

{% endblock %}
